Not true. With the MB cap, you only need X mana to be able to cap the damage. If you have &gt; X mana, then you don't need to be FM to still be able to do max MB damage. Now you can &quot;soften up&quot; your target with a couple of lures, then blast them dead with MB. Now instead of 1 shot kills, you will have to live with 2 shot kills.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Modified several of the Planes of Power alternate entry quests to make completing them faster. Also, all of these quests will now give a &quot;key&quot; to everyone in the group of the person that completes it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Wow. This is a HUGE change. This will make if way easier to get entire guilds access to tier 2/3. Making them &quot;faster&quot; and making them &quot;key&quot; 6 people at a time should be good for a flood of people into the higher tiers.<br>
<br>
Now for what everyone though was going to be the &quot;huge charm nerf&quot;. What a joke.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Healing a charmed pet now generates an appropriate amount of hate for the healer.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
This won't affect charm killing one bit. Any smart charm killer lets the pet get close to 0% health so they can get a free kill when they break charm.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Charmed pets now take up to one third of the experience for each NPC killed<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Boo hoo. At worst that means that a charm killer will get an AA in 45min instead of 15min. Spend a little mana to do some damage and that number will drop. This does not prevent people from being able to pull off solo kills of BoT bosses.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Charmed pets are no longer selected as a monster's preferred target if there are many players available for the monster to attack instead<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
How about when there is only 1 player to attack???<br>
<br>
Oh well, good for the chanters. I thought the proposed changes where ridiculous anyway.<br>
<br>
Overall, not a bad patch, not a good one. Hope they didn't screw up bards too bad. <p><div align="center" class="font-size: 11px; font-family: arial">
