Ok, read that paragraph again and tell me if I'm crazy.<br>
<br>
Possible ways this could work:<br>
1) Damage is capped before resists are taken into account - but is it capped before <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>crits</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> are taken into account?  (I believe crits are calculated after resists, are they not?)<br>
2) HP Buffs: ok, this one is extremely unlikely, but the use of the wording &quot;fully healed&quot; and no mention of buffs makes me wonder if the 75% cap is calculated based on base+equipment HP and not necessarily counting direct HP buffs.  If so, the cap could end up being closer to 50% of actual buffed HP.<br>
<br>
Just a couple of things to test out if you're interested - SOE tends to muck things up occasionally, after all... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kaelonxerxentis>Kaelon Xerxentis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.boomspeed.com/kaelon/wand.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/8/03 12:06:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25839.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.kaelon.com/images/kaehead.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Patch Message. 4/8</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>** Illusions/Shape Change **<br>
